<div id="tab-skincancer" class="tab-panel">
  <div class="section-header">
    <h2><span data-lang="en">Recognising signs of skin cancer</span><span data-lang="zh">识别皮肤癌的征兆</span><span data-lang="ko">피부암 징후 인식하기</span><span data-lang="ja">皮膚がんのサインを知る</span></h2>
    <p><span data-lang="en">Australia has one of the highest rates of skin cancer in the world. Between 95–99% of skin cancers are caused by UV exposure — making sun protection a direct form of cancer prevention.</span><span data-lang="zh">澳大利亚是世界上皮肤癌发病率最高的国家之一。95–99%的皮肤癌由紫外线暴露引起，因此防晒直接预防癌症。</span><span data-lang="ko">호주는 세계에서 피부암 발생률이 가장 높은 나라 중 하나입니다. 피부암의 95~99%가 자외선 노출로 인해 발생합니다.</span><span data-lang="ja">オーストラリアは世界で最も皮膚がんの発生率が高い国の一つです。皮膚がんの95〜99%はUV暴露が原因です。</span></p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title"><span data-lang="en">Skin cancer in Australia</span><span data-lang="zh">澳大利亚皮肤癌概况</span><span data-lang="ko">호주의 피부암 현황</span><span data-lang="ja">オーストラリアの皮膚がん</span></div>
    <div class="sc-stats-grid">
      <div class="sc-stat"><div class="sc-stat-num">2 in 3</div><div class="sc-stat-label"><span data-lang="en">Australians diagnosed with skin cancer in their lifetime</span><span data-lang="zh">澳大利亚人一生中被诊断出皮肤癌</span><span data-lang="ko">호주인이 평생 피부암 진단을 받음</span><span data-lang="ja">オーストラリア人が生涯に皮膚がんと診断される</span></div></div>
      <div class="sc-stat"><div class="sc-stat-num">~18,200</div><div class="sc-stat-label"><span data-lang="en">Melanoma diagnoses in Australia in 2023</span><span data-lang="zh">2023年澳大利亚黑色素瘤诊断数</span><span data-lang="ko">2023년 호주 흑색종 진단 건수</span><span data-lang="ja">2023年のオーストラリアのメラノーマ診断数</span></div></div>
      <div class="sc-stat"><div class="sc-stat-num">1 in 17</div><div class="sc-stat-label"><span data-lang="en">Australians will be diagnosed with melanoma by age 85</span><span data-lang="zh">澳大利亚人在85岁前将被诊断出黑色素瘤</span><span data-lang="ko">호주인이 85세까지 흑색종 진단을 받음</span><span data-lang="ja">85歳までにメラノーマと診断される</span></div></div>
      <div class="sc-stat"><div class="sc-stat-num">1.1M+</div><div class="sc-stat-label"><span data-lang="en">Non-melanoma skin cancer treatments given annually in Australia</span><span data-lang="zh">澳大利亚每年进行的非黑色素瘤皮肤癌治疗</span><span data-lang="ko">호주에서 매년 시행되는 비흑색종 피부암 치료 건수</span><span data-lang="ja">オーストラリアで毎年行われる非メラノーマ皮膚がん治療数</span></div></div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-light);margin-top:12px;"><span data-lang="en">Sources: Cancer Council Australia (2024); AIHW Cancer data in Australia 2024; Australian Skin Cancer Foundation.</span><span data-lang="zh">来源：澳大利亚癌症委员会（2024）；AIHW 2024年澳大利亚癌症数据；澳大利亚皮肤癌基金会。</span><span data-lang="ko">출처: Cancer Council Australia(2024); AIHW 2024년 암 데이터; 호주 피부암 재단.</span><span data-lang="ja">出典：Cancer Council Australia（2024）；AIHW がんデータ2024；オーストラリア皮膚がん財団。</span></p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title"><span data-lang="en">The three main types of skin cancer</span><span data-lang="zh">三种主要皮肤癌类型</span><span data-lang="ko">세 가지 주요 피부암 유형</span><span data-lang="ja">皮膚がんの3つの主な種類</span></div>
    <div class="sc-types-grid">
      <div class="sc-type-card bcc">
        <div class="sc-type-title"><span data-lang="en">Basal Cell Carcinoma</span><span data-lang="zh">基底细胞癌</span><span data-lang="ko">기저세포암</span><span data-lang="ja">基底細胞がん</span></div>
        <div class="sc-type-subtitle"><span data-lang="en">BCC — most common, least dangerous</span><span data-lang="zh">BCC — 最常见，危险性最低</span><span data-lang="ko">BCC — 가장 흔하고 위험성 낮음</span><span data-lang="ja">BCC — 最も一般的で危険性が低い</span></div>
        <div class="sc-type-body"><span data-lang="en">Accounts for about 70% of non-melanoma skin cancers. Grows slowly and rarely spreads. Develops most commonly on the head, face, neck, shoulders and back.</span><span data-lang="zh">约占非黑色素瘤皮肤癌的70%。生长缓慢，很少扩散。最常发生在头部、面部、颈部、肩部和背部。</span><span data-lang="ko">비흑색종 피부암의 약 70%를 차지합니다. 천천히 자라며 거의 퍼지지 않습니다. 머리, 얼굴, 목, 어깨, 등에 주로 발생합니다.</span><span data-lang="ja">非メラノーマ皮膚がんの約70%を占めます。ゆっくりと成長し、ほとんど転移しません。</span></div>
        <div class="sc-type-signs"><strong><span data-lang="en">Warning signs</span><span data-lang="zh">警告征兆</span><span data-lang="ko">경고 징후</span><span data-lang="ja">警告サイン</span></strong><div><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">Pearly or waxy bump</span><span data-lang="zh">珍珠状或蜡状肿块</span><span data-lang="ko">진주빛 또는 납빛 융기</span><span data-lang="ja">真珠色のしこり</span></span><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">Flat flesh-coloured lesion</span><span data-lang="zh">扁平肉色病变</span><span data-lang="ko">편평한 살색 병변</span><span data-lang="ja">平らな肌色の病変</span></span><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">Bleeding or scabbing sore</span><span data-lang="zh">出血或结痂的溃疡</span><span data-lang="ko">출혈 또는 딱지 생기는 상처</span><span data-lang="ja">出血またはかさぶたのある傷</span></span><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">Sore that heals and returns</span><span data-lang="zh">愈合后复发的溃疡</span><span data-lang="ko">낫다가 다시 생기는 상처</span><span data-lang="ja">治っては再発する傷</span></span></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="sc-type-card scc">
        <div class="sc-type-title"><span data-lang="en">Squamous Cell Carcinoma</span><span data-lang="zh">鳞状细胞癌</span><span data-lang="ko">편평세포암</span><span data-lang="ja">扁平上皮がん</span></div>
        <div class="sc-type-subtitle"><span data-lang="en">SCC — second most common, can spread</span><span data-lang="zh">SCC — 第二常见，可能扩散</span><span data-lang="ko">SCC — 두 번째로 흔하고 전이 가능</span><span data-lang="ja">SCC — 2番目に一般的、転移の可能性あり</span></div>
        <div class="sc-type-body"><span data-lang="en">About 30% of non-melanoma skin cancers. Grows quickly over weeks or months. Appears on sun-exposed areas — head, neck, hands, forearms. Can spread if untreated.</span><span data-lang="zh">约占非黑色素瘤皮肤癌的30%。在数周或数月内快速生长。出现在日晒部位——头部、颈部、手部、前臂。若不治疗可能扩散。</span><span data-lang="ko">비흑색종 피부암의 약 30%를 차지합니다. 수주 또는 수개월에 걸쳐 빠르게 자랍니다. 치료하지 않으면 퍼질 수 있습니다.</span><span data-lang="ja">非メラノーマ皮膚がんの約30%を占めます。急速に成長します。放置すると転移する可能性があります。</span></div>
        <div class="sc-type-signs"><strong><span data-lang="en">Warning signs</span><span data-lang="zh">警告征兆</span><span data-lang="ko">경고 징후</span><span data-lang="ja">警告サイン</span></strong><div><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">Firm red nodule</span><span data-lang="zh">坚实的红色结节</span><span data-lang="ko">단단한 붉은 결절</span><span data-lang="ja">硬い赤い結節</span></span><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">Thickened red scaly spot</span><span data-lang="zh">增厚的红色鳞状斑点</span><span data-lang="ko">두꺼워진 붉고 비늘 같은 반점</span><span data-lang="ja">肥厚した赤いうろこ状の斑点</span></span><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">Flat lesion with crusted surface</span><span data-lang="zh">表面结痂的扁平病变</span><span data-lang="ko">딱지 있는 편평한 병변</span><span data-lang="ja">かさぶた状の表面を持つ病変</span></span><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">Rough wart-like growth</span><span data-lang="zh">粗糙的疣状增生</span><span data-lang="ko">거칠고 사마귀 같은 성장물</span><span data-lang="ja">粗いいぼ状の増殖</span></span></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="sc-type-card mel">
        <div class="sc-type-title"><span data-lang="en">Melanoma</span><span data-lang="zh">黑色素瘤</span><span data-lang="ko">흑색종</span><span data-lang="ja">メラノーマ</span></div>
        <div class="sc-type-subtitle"><span data-lang="en">Most serious — can spread rapidly</span><span data-lang="zh">最严重——可能迅速扩散</span><span data-lang="ko">가장 심각 — 빠르게 전이 가능</span><span data-lang="ja">最も深刻 — 急速に転移する可能性あり</span></div>
        <div class="sc-type-body"><span data-lang="en">Rarest but most dangerous. Can occur on any part of the body, including areas never exposed to the sun. When detected early, the 5-year survival rate is 99%.</span><span data-lang="zh">最罕见但最危险。可发生在身体任何部位，包括从未暴露于阳光的部位。早期发现时，5年生存率为99%。</span><span data-lang="ko">가장 드물지만 가장 위험합니다. 햇볕이 닿지 않는 부위를 포함한 신체 어느 곳에서나 발생할 수 있습니다. 조기 발견 시 5년 생존율은 99%입니다.</span><span data-lang="ja">最もまれですが最も危険です。早期発見時の5年生存率は99%です。</span></div>
        <div class="sc-type-signs"><strong><span data-lang="en">Warning signs</span><span data-lang="zh">警告征兆</span><span data-lang="ko">경고 징후</span><span data-lang="ja">警告サイン</span></strong><div><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">Change in existing mole</span><span data-lang="zh">现有痣的变化</span><span data-lang="ko">기존 점의 변화</span><span data-lang="ja">既存のほくろの変化</span></span><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">New unusual spot</span><span data-lang="zh">新的异常斑点</span><span data-lang="ko">새로운 비정상적인 반점</span><span data-lang="ja">新しい異常な斑点</span></span><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">Itching, bleeding or crusting</span><span data-lang="zh">瘙痒、出血或结痂</span><span data-lang="ko">가려움, 출혈 또는 딱지</span><span data-lang="ja">かゆみ、出血、かさぶた</span></span><span class="sc-sign-pill"><span data-lang="en">Multi-coloured lesion</span><span data-lang="zh">多色病变</span><span data-lang="ko">다색 병변</span><span data-lang="ja">多色の病変</span></span></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-light);margin-top:14px;"><span data-lang="en">Sources: Cancer Council Australia — Understanding Skin Cancer (Jan 2024); Healthdirect Australia; Cancer Council WA.</span><span data-lang="zh">来源：澳大利亚癌症委员会——了解皮肤癌（2024年1月）；澳大利亚健康直通；西澳癌症委员会。</span><span data-lang="ko">출처: Cancer Council Australia(2024년 1월); Healthdirect Australia; Cancer Council WA.</span><span data-lang="ja">出典：Cancer Council Australia（2024年1月）；Healthdirect Australia；Cancer Council WA。</span></p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title"><span data-lang="en">The ABCDE rule — checking for melanoma</span><span data-lang="zh">ABCDE原则——检查黑色素瘤</span><span data-lang="ko">ABCDE 규칙 — 흑색종 확인</span><span data-lang="ja">ABCDEルール — メラノーマのチェック</span></div>
    <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:16px;"><span data-lang="en">Used by Cancer Council Australia and dermatologists to identify suspicious spots. Check any mole or spot against all five criteria.</span><span data-lang="zh">由澳大利亚癌症委员会和皮肤科医生用于识别可疑斑点。对照所有五个标准检查任何痣或斑点。</span><span data-lang="ko">Cancer Council Australia와 피부과 의사들이 의심스러운 반점을 식별하는 데 사용합니다.</span><span data-lang="ja">Cancer Council Australiaと皮膚科医が不審な斑点を特定するために使用します。</span></p>
    <div class="abcde-grid">
      <div class="abcde-card"><div class="abcde-letter">A</div><div class="abcde-word"><span data-lang="en">Asymmetry</span><span data-lang="zh">不对称</span><span data-lang="ko">비대칭</span><span data-lang="ja">非対称</span></div><div class="abcde-desc"><span data-lang="en">One half does not match the other half in shape or size.</span><span data-lang="zh">一半与另一半形状或大小不匹配。</span><span data-lang="ko">한쪽이 다른 쪽과 형태나 크기가 일치하지 않습니다.</span><span data-lang="ja">一方の半分がもう一方と一致しない。</span></div></div>
      <div class="abcde-card"><div class="abcde-letter">B</div><div class="abcde-word"><span data-lang="en">Border</span><span data-lang="zh">边缘</span><span data-lang="ko">경계</span><span data-lang="ja">境界</span></div><div class="abcde-desc"><span data-lang="en">Edges are irregular, ragged, notched or blurred. Pigment may spread into surrounding skin.</span><span data-lang="zh">边缘不规则、参差不齐、有缺口或模糊。色素可能蔓延到周围皮肤。</span><span data-lang="ko">가장자리가 불규칙하거나 들쭉날쭉하거나 흐릿합니다.</span><span data-lang="ja">縁が不規則、ぎざぎざ、またはぼやけている。</span></div></div>
      <div class="abcde-card"><div class="abcde-letter">C</div><div class="abcde-word"><span data-lang="en">Colour</span><span data-lang="zh">颜色</span><span data-lang="ko">색상</span><span data-lang="ja">色</span></div><div class="abcde-desc"><span data-lang="en">Multiple colours in one lesion — shades of brown, black, red, white or blue.</span><span data-lang="zh">一个病变中有多种颜色——棕色、黑色、红色、白色或蓝色。</span><span data-lang="ko">하나의 병변에 여러 색상 — 갈색, 검정, 빨강, 흰색 또는 파란색.</span><span data-lang="ja">一つの病変に複数の色 — 茶色、黒、赤、白、または青。</span></div></div>
      <div class="abcde-card"><div class="abcde-letter">D</div><div class="abcde-word"><span data-lang="en">Diameter</span><span data-lang="zh">直径</span><span data-lang="ko">지름</span><span data-lang="ja">直径</span></div><div class="abcde-desc"><span data-lang="en">Larger than 6mm (pencil eraser), or smaller but growing. Any enlarging spot deserves attention.</span><span data-lang="zh">大于6毫米（铅笔橡皮擦），或更小但正在增大。</span><span data-lang="ko">6mm(연필 지우개)보다 크거나, 더 작지만 커지고 있습니다.</span><span data-lang="ja">6mm（鉛筆の消しゴム）より大きい、またはより小さいが成長中。</span></div></div>
      <div class="abcde-card"><div class="abcde-letter">E</div><div class="abcde-word"><span data-lang="en">Evolving</span><span data-lang="zh">演变</span><span data-lang="ko">변화</span><span data-lang="ja">変化</span></div><div class="abcde-desc"><span data-lang="en">Any change in size, shape, colour or new symptoms such as itching, bleeding or crusting.</span><span data-lang="zh">大小、形状、颜色的任何变化，或瘙痒、出血或结痂等新症状。</span><span data-lang="ko">크기, 모양, 색상의 변화 또는 가려움, 출혈, 딱지 등 새로운 증상.</span><span data-lang="ja">サイズ、形、色の変化、またはかゆみ、出血、かさぶたなどの新しい症状。</span></div></div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-light);margin-top:14px;"><span data-lang="en">Source: Cancer Council Australia — Melanoma (May 2024 medical review); American Cancer Society.</span><span data-lang="zh">来源：澳大利亚癌症委员会——黑色素瘤（2024年5月医学审查）；美国癌症协会。</span><span data-lang="ko">출처: Cancer Council Australia — 흑색종(2024년 5월); 미국 암학회.</span><span data-lang="ja">出典：Cancer Council Australia — メラノーマ（2024年5月）；米国がん協会。</span></p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title"><span data-lang="en">The EFG rule — nodular melanoma</span><span data-lang="zh">EFG原则——结节性黑色素瘤</span><span data-lang="ko">EFG 규칙 — 결절성 흑색종</span><span data-lang="ja">EFGルール — 結節性メラノーマ</span></div>
    <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:14px;"><span data-lang="en">Nodular melanoma accounts for about 15% of melanoma in Australia. It is aggressive, grows rapidly, and may not follow the ABCDE pattern — it can appear symmetrical and dome-shaped.</span><span data-lang="zh">结节性黑色素瘤约占澳大利亚黑色素瘤的15%。它具有侵袭性，生长迅速，可能不符合ABCDE模式。</span><span data-lang="ko">결절성 흑색종은 호주 흑색종의 약 15%를 차지합니다. 공격적이고 빠르게 자라며 ABCDE 패턴을 따르지 않을 수 있습니다.</span><span data-lang="ja">結節性メラノーマはオーストラリアのメラノーマの約15%を占めます。侵攻性が高く、ABCDEパターンに従わない場合があります。</span></p>
    <div class="efg-bar">
      <div class="efg-item"><div class="efg-letter">E</div><div class="efg-word"><span data-lang="en">Elevated</span><span data-lang="zh">隆起</span><span data-lang="ko">융기</span><span data-lang="ja">隆起</span></div><div class="efg-desc"><span data-lang="en">The spot is raised above the skin surface</span><span data-lang="zh">斑点高出皮肤表面</span><span data-lang="ko">반점이 피부 표면 위로 솟아 있음</span><span data-lang="ja">斑点が皮膚表面より隆起している</span></div></div>
      <div class="efg-item"><div class="efg-letter">F</div><div class="efg-word"><span data-lang="en">Firm</span><span data-lang="zh">坚实</span><span data-lang="ko">단단함</span><span data-lang="ja">硬い</span></div><div class="efg-desc"><span data-lang="en">The spot feels firm or solid to the touch</span><span data-lang="zh">触摸时感觉坚硬或实心</span><span data-lang="ko">만졌을 때 단단하거나 딱딱하게 느껴짐</span><span data-lang="ja">触ると硬いまたは固く感じる</span></div></div>
      <div class="efg-item"><div class="efg-letter">G</div><div class="efg-word"><span data-lang="en">Growing</span><span data-lang="zh">增长</span><span data-lang="ko">성장</span><span data-lang="ja">成長</span></div><div class="efg-desc"><span data-lang="en">The spot has grown noticeably over 3–4 weeks</span><span data-lang="zh">斑点在3–4周内明显增大</span><span data-lang="ko">반점이 3~4주 내에 눈에 띄게 커짐</span><span data-lang="ja">斑点が3〜4週間で著しく成長している</span></div></div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-light);margin-top:12px;"><span data-lang="en">Source: MoleMap Australia — Signs of Skin Cancer: ABCDEFG Guidelines; Cancer Council Australia (2024).</span><span data-lang="zh">来源：MoleMap澳大利亚——皮肤癌征兆：ABCDEFG指南；澳大利亚癌症委员会（2024）。</span><span data-lang="ko">출처: MoleMap Australia — ABCDEFG 지침; Cancer Council Australia(2024).</span><span data-lang="ja">出典：MoleMap Australia — ABCDEFGガイドライン；Cancer Council Australia（2024）。</span></p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title"><span data-lang="en">How to do a monthly skin self-check</span><span data-lang="zh">如何进行每月皮肤自我检查</span><span data-lang="ko">월간 피부 자가 검진 방법</span><span data-lang="ja">月1回の皮膚自己チェックの方法</span></div>
    <div class="sc-checklist">
      <div class="sc-check"><span class="sc-check-icon">🪞</span><span data-lang="en"><strong>Use a full-length mirror</strong> in a well-lit room. Examine your entire body front and back, then left and right sides with arms raised.</span><span data-lang="zh"><strong>在光线充足的房间使用全身镜</strong>。检查身体前后，然后举起手臂检查左右两侧。</span><span data-lang="ko"><strong>밝은 방에서 전신 거울을 사용하세요</strong>. 몸의 앞뒤를 검사한 다음 팔을 들어 좌우를 검사하세요.</span><span data-lang="ja"><strong>明るい部屋で全身鏡を使用してください</strong>。体の前後を検査し、次に腕を上げて左右を検査します。</span></div>
      <div class="sc-check"><span class="sc-check-icon">🔍</span><span data-lang="en"><strong>Check hard-to-see areas</strong> including your scalp, back of neck, between toes, soles of feet, and under fingernails and toenails.</span><span data-lang="zh"><strong>检查难以看到的区域</strong>，包括头皮、颈后、脚趾之间、脚底、指甲和趾甲下方。</span><span data-lang="ko"><strong>보기 어려운 부위를 확인하세요</strong> — 두피, 목 뒤, 발가락 사이, 발바닥, 손발톱 아래 포함.</span><span data-lang="ja"><strong>見えにくい部位を確認してください</strong> — 頭皮、首の後ろ、足の指の間、足の裏、爪の下。</span></div>
      <div class="sc-check"><span class="sc-check-icon">📸</span><span data-lang="en"><strong>Photograph any suspicious spots</strong> so you can track changes over time. Show the photo to your GP or pharmacist if you are unsure.</span><span data-lang="zh"><strong>拍摄任何可疑斑点</strong>，以便随时间追踪变化。如不确定，请将照片展示给全科医生或药剂师。</span><span data-lang="ko"><strong>의심스러운 반점을 사진으로 찍어두세요</strong>. 확실하지 않으면 GP나 약사에게 사진을 보여주세요.</span><span data-lang="ja"><strong>疑わしい斑点を写真に撮ってください</strong>。不明な場合はGPまたは薬剤師に写真を見せてください。</span></div>
      <div class="sc-check"><span class="sc-check-icon">🏥</span><span data-lang="en"><strong>Book an annual professional skin check</strong> with your GP or a skin cancer clinic, especially if you have fair skin, a history of sunburn, or many moles.</span><span data-lang="zh"><strong>每年预约专业皮肤检查</strong>，特别是皮肤白皙、有晒伤史或痣多的人。</span><span data-lang="ko"><strong>매년 전문 피부 검진을 예약하세요</strong> — 특히 피부가 밝거나 일광화상 이력이 있거나 점이 많은 경우.</span><span data-lang="ja"><strong>毎年専門的な皮膚検査を予約してください</strong> — 特に色白の肌、日焼けの歴史、またはほくろが多い場合。</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="alert alert-danger">
    <strong><span data-lang="en">When to seek urgent attention — </span><span data-lang="zh">何时寻求紧急帮助 — </span><span data-lang="ko">즉각적인 주의가 필요한 경우 — </span><span data-lang="ja">緊急の注意が必要な場合 — </span></strong>
    <span data-lang="en">See your GP as soon as possible if you notice a spot meeting any ABCDE criteria, a sore that does not heal within a few weeks, any spot that bleeds without injury, or any growth that looks different from all other spots on your body (the "ugly duckling" sign).</span>
    <span data-lang="zh">如果发现符合任何ABCDE标准的斑点、数周内未愈合的溃疡、无故出血的斑点，或看起来与身体其他所有斑点不同的增生（"丑小鸭"征兆），请尽快就医。</span>
    <span data-lang="ko">ABCDE 기준을 충족하는 반점, 몇 주 내에 낫지 않는 상처, 부상 없이 출혈이 있는 반점, 또는 신체의 다른 모든 반점과 다르게 보이는 성장물("못생긴 오리새끼" 징후)이 있으면 가능한 한 빨리 GP를 방문하세요.</span>
    <span data-lang="ja">ABCDE基準のいずれかを満たす斑点、数週間以内に治らない傷、怪我なく出血する斑点、または体の他のすべての斑点と異なって見える増殖（「みにくいアヒルの子」サイン）に気づいた場合は、できるだけ早くGPを受診してください。</span>
  </div>
